laboratory_examinations.findings: Values: NO GROWTH. Reference range: 5.0 - 8.0 units. Measurement: 7.0 units.

No acute intracranial hemorrhage, edema, mass effect, or vascular territorial infarct. Ventricles and sulci are normal in size and morphology. Gray-white matter differentiation is preserved. Calcifications are noted in the cavernous carotid and vertebral arteries.
